==|| INTRODUCTION
Calculations were done on the './archive_7' directory in the git repository 'hmofa' @ https://github.com/Azuhmier/hmofa . Thus one can clone the repository themselves and either check the calculations themselves or even do more things with them. However I have not yet learned to 'scrape' sofurry and A03 for their stories. Last time i played around with the sofurry API, it would only let me query and really only easily access stories of users who had "writer" in their profile. I have not checked back to see if this is still the case.

Anonymous Mon 22 Mar 2021 16:31:16 No.37300499 Report
Quoted By: >>37301677
>>37300391
Try and take a concept that is or can be trimmed down to a managable size. Something that can be written start to finish in a few sessions. A short story that has all the essentials of what you are trying to do, but doesn't stretch itself to infinity.

I know it's easier said than done, but try and make a story that is limited enough that it only takes a few pages.

If you are afraid (like I were) of "wasting" good characters, worldbuilding or plots on a project you don't know you can handle, don't be. You will have many ideas vastly superior to anything you are attached to right now in the future.

Sorry for being so presumptuous, but I thought this was good advice in general.

"Demios" Format, or "Demios" for short, is a txt format centered around archiveing/listing pastebin stories. The following Assumptions are made:
1) For Name 'x' there exists a range from 1 --> xu
2) For TITLE/URL pair 'y' there exists a range from 1 --> yu_x
3) x = 0, is reserved for all TITLE/URL pairs without a corresponding NAME

----------------------------------------------------------
By {NAME_1}
>{TITLE_1.1}
{URL_1.1}
...
>{TITLE_1.y}
{URL_1.y}
...
>{TITLE_1.yu_1}
{URL_1.yu_1}
----------------------------------------------------------
...
----------------------------------------------------------
By {NAME_x}
>{TITLE_x.1}
{URL_x.1}
...
>{TITLE_x.y}
{URL_x.y}
...
>{TITLE_x.yu_x}
{URL_x.yu_x}
----------------------------------------------------------
...
----------------------------------------------------------
By {NAME_xu}
>{TITLE_xu.1}
{URL_xu.1}
...
>{TITLE_xu.y}
{URL_xu.y}
...
>{TITLE_xu.yu_xu}
{URL_xu.yu_xu}
----------------------------------------------------------
By {NAME_0}
>{TITLE_0.1}
{URL_0.1}
...
>{TITLE_0.y}
{URL_0.y}
...
>{TITLE_0.yu_0}
{URL_0.yu_0}
----------------------------------------------------------
